modules.description: Sleeps for a specified number of nanoseconds using a non-blocking, asynchronous approach. Operates on 64-bit integers to represent time durations. Useful for precise timing in event-driven applications, such as delaying network requests or synchronizing asynchronous tasks.

Handles parsing and serialization of DHCP protocol messages, including options and message types. Works with byte sequences, IP addresses, and DHCP message structures. Used to process incoming DHCP requests and generate appropriate responses in networked applications.

Provides precise, non-blocking sleep operations using 64-bit integer time durations, enabling accurate timing in asynchronous workflows. Supports delaying network interactions and coordinating event-driven processes. Accepts nanosecond values for fine-grained control over execution pauses. Can be used to implement retry logic, rate limiting, or timed state transitions in network clients.
